A case of business robbery has been opened after five men stormed into a petrol station and bombed its safe in Crystal Park, Benoni, in Ekurhuleni. Crystal Park police spokesperson Tryna Maritz said: Two suspects had rifles and three others were armed with handguns. They were wearing balaclavas. Maritz said no shots were fired and no injuries reported during the incident, which occurred on Wednesday, Benoni City Times reported. The Germiston Explosive Unit took over the scene after the initial SAPS inspection, she added. The suspects escaped with cigarettes and an undisclosed amount of cash. No arrests had been made. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter .